Date: 24/2/1912
Source: NZ Truth
Author:
Vol / Page: 6
Edition:
Quote: The `bach,' said the doctor was absolutely unfit for human habitation. ... The owner of the place, who used to draw three shillings a week in rent for the rotten crib, was feverishly engaged in pulling it down on the following day.
Notes:  [Christchurch reference: is this an intermediate use, between<i>crib</i>, a sub-standard or makeshift dwelling-place, and <i>bach</i>, in the older sense of a `lean-to' or a `whare']

